{
  "abstract": "CHICKPEA (Cicer arietinum L.) is a highly self-pollinated crop and the scope for\r\nexploitation of hybrid vigour will depend on the direction and magnitude of\r\nheterosis, biological feasibility and the type of gene action involved. Also,\r\nstudy of heterosis will have a direct bearing on the breeding methodology to\r\nbe employed for varietal improvement. There is limited published data on\r\nheterosis in chickpea.",
